         Vazaelle is what I like to call a 'right wing anti-smoker'.  He just 'dont want any of them smokers in his nieburhood'...</P><P>Do you know the amount of Carbon gasses released into your car when you start your engine in the morning is equivelent to someone smoking an entire pack of cigarrettes right in your face in about 10 seconds?</P><P>If people are so concerned about their airspace, they should stop driving their cars... because our cars will produce more cancer causing pollution in a year than a smoker in an entire lifetime of smoking... and yes people DO have to breathe the fumes caused by your car, they dont just magically dissapear, especially when you live ina city like Phoenix where the air gets trapped in the valley here.</P><P>Also, the age demographics of people that DIE from smoking are kind of ... questionable.  No doubt smoking IS bad for your health and WILL reduce the quality of your old age (and breath, blech), but did you know only it only takes on average about 7 years off your life?  You will still likely live to see 70 years of age if you are a smoker... smoking kills?  Personally, I dont know that I want to live past 70-75, if you spend 10 minutes in a nursing home you will know why I say that.</P><P>We like to keep our old people alive to almost freakish levels.  By the time my Grandfather died (at 90), he was in a wheelchair, blind, deaf, and just sat blankly for hours everyday... sorry I dont want that.  </P><P>And if people are going to use the "dont spend my tax dollar on your smoking healthcare" arguement, you might also remember that keeping someone alive in nursing care for 7+ years beyond a smoker is going to cost the taxpayers far more than if they died from smoking.  It's a morbid thought, and I dont like attaching money to it, but the anti-smoking freaks like to throw that stupid money line out there, it's just not true.</P><P><BR>Xuraz Xorthexia - <BR>Warlock<BR>Xegony Server<BR>Profile - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/